						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>/sigh</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I will be frank.&nbsp; I have had alot of fun in EQ over the past 4 years playing and i've made alot of friends too.&nbsp;&nbsp;Having leveled at least 2 chars up to 65 and a few others up tot he 60s, i've seen alot of things come and go over the years.&nbsp; I remember when druids and necros had dots nerfed because people cried about how they could get exp soloing!&nbsp; *GASP* That was so evil that SoE saw fit to nerf dot damage to where if the mob was moving on the dot cycle, the dot would do half damage.&nbsp; This was later removed to allow the dot to do full damager after SoE saw how ill conceived this "fix" was, but the "fix" they are using on PBAoE is par for the course for SoE.&nbsp; Nothing has changed.&nbsp; The "fix" they used on dot kiters then was wrong, and it is wrong to do what they are doing to bards now.&nbsp; Before you&nbsp;brand me as&nbsp;a macroer, let me assure you I have AoE kited for exp maybe 2 times in my 4 years.&nbsp; The one time I succesfully kited a group of mobs to death, I think I earned 1/3 of an AA exp doing it.&nbsp; It took me roughly 15-20 minutes to do it too, not the mention the fact that I died at least twice before that while attempting the same kite.&nbsp; That exp was pathetic.&nbsp; I could hve gotten&nbsp;a hell of alot more exp doing a tipt or KT exp group/run, and it was worth nowhere near the risk of dying midway through a kite to lose all the time put into the kite.&nbsp; This may not be a problem with macroers as they can probably do this w/o risk, but for your&nbsp;average player who doesn't break the rules, this nerf is uncalled for and rediculous.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Almost all of the AoE kiting i've done, has been for farming of tradeskill components or bone chips and the like.&nbsp; Anyone who has done lots of tradeskills knows how tedious this is, and I found that AoE kiting was one of the best tools to help keep the tedium to a minimum.&nbsp; Now, with this fix, we can no longer us this for this purpose.&nbsp; Mobs, even if they are green, in a large group can bash the bard to where he can't play a thing, thus making it impossible even if hes standing still, to use the songs.&nbsp; Being a paper tank, the bard will die before he could kill the mobs with AoEs now.&nbsp; PBAoEs with this fix are now virtually worthless.&nbsp; You wont be using them in any KT+ groups thats for sure, and if you do, you will be ejected from the group soon after your group is done doing its CR run.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Month after month, bards keep getting nerfed again and again, with no compensation for their decreased soloability or decreased utility.&nbsp; Maybe it is our uber&nbsp;level 64 charm that lets us charm level&nbsp;57 mobs that made up for all the nerfage, who knows.&nbsp; You would think they could make the songs that are being nerfed to something extra to make up for the nerf, but no.&nbsp; It is not within their "vision" to compensate for nerfs.&nbsp; We shall eat our slop they serve and like it.&nbsp; Add to all this, the fact that my other level 65, the necro, his epic 2.0 will have of all things, a spell agro reducing focus.&nbsp; Oh joy of joys, I can't wait, especially since I can just FD now anyway to lose agro.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Sony just never ceases to amaze me with how they "fix" things sometimes.&nbsp; Instead of going after macroers or people who gather up 50+ mobs and kite them around, they hit every bard with the nerf bat because of a few morons.&nbsp; Way to&nbsp;swing at&nbsp;the fly with the nerf bat SoE.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I was hoping to stick around until after omens, and level my two 65s up to level 70, but with the latest round of nerfs and dissapointments, I think its time to hang the bone chips and the horn up, especially with WoW on the horizon.&nbsp; I may return someday, but four years is a long long time to have been playing one game.&nbsp; To those that keep playing, I wish you the best and hope bards get some really cool new toys in the future, and to the inevitable morons who ask if they can have my stuff: No, go out and earn it yourself like I did.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-SR</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
