 ago.  I think this change is a bit extreme, but given how exploitable this was, I see no alternative.  Yes, it sucks for those that legitimately ae kited.  However, those that did ae kite should realize how overpowered it was.</FONT></DIV><DIV><FONT color=#ffffff></FONT> </DIV><DIV><FONT color=#ffffff>I congratulate the developers for finally tackling this issue, irrespective of the uproar.  If only they would have done this on more issues in the past.</FONT></DIV></BLOCKQUOTE><DIV></DIV><br><hr></blockquote><br><br><br><br>Necro hree, and I can avg about 4-5 aa an hour charm kiting.  Just for the record, I'm supporting the bards here.  Wanna make it even?  Only let their AE's hit up to 4 mobs... or make their AE's require a very VERY minimal amt of mana that increases substantialy per mob caught in the song?  Just my two cp.  Yes tho, necros and chanters can make just as much exp...  *ducks the nerf bat*<br><br>Paegar<br>Firiona Vie
																		
