<DIV>There are only a handful of places where AE kiting massive amount of mobs... and the Devs are smoking crack if we didn't KNOW they were designed for AE kiting.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I mean come on:&nbsp; LoY = lots and lots of same running speed, non-casting, non-summoning mobs in wide open flat areas.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So instead of adding the element of a rooting mob here, a summoning mob there, a tree and a rock here and there, they are taking away a class defining ability.&nbsp; It's BS pure and simple.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If your content for OoW can be exploited by AE kiting bards... do I need to fill in the blanks?&nbsp; Add a rooting mob here, a summoning mob there, a tree and a rock here and there.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>SOE Dev's had a choice:&nbsp; Make minor changes to content, or nerf bards and when it came down to it they thought the better option was to screw the players rather than sully up someone's work with trees, rocks, casters, and summoning mobs.&nbsp; God forbid you should design content around gameplay... no no no... change gameplay to fit content... ahh yes that works!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Last I knew of you cannot AE kite PoF tables.&nbsp; The best AE exp place is Nadox because you can kill like 100 mobs at at time.&nbsp; And one kite nets you about 75% AAxp every 20 minutes (so I've heard).&nbsp; Would a developer have to stay past 4:30 or skip his daily Mario-cart break to add 12 rooting mobs to that area?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Wizards can quad PoF tables.</DIV>
<DIV>Druids can quad PoF tables.</DIV>
<DIV>Chanter risk, is an anthill when compared to AE kiting, and the reward is monumentally greater.</DIV>
<DIV>Necros eat exp for breakfast.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Bards are not the #1 exp gainers, but we are the only ones being hit with the nerf bat... and the nerf not only effects uses that SOE has deemed bad, but also other more benign uses such at TS farming, factioning, and limited raid usage.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The tons of loot that bards aquire from AE kiting gets sold to vendors... yeah 100 Zxathril forged cutlasses... UBER!&nbsp; What about a necro that solos boots of flowing slime camp and nets a pair of 200kpp boots? (yes I'm very jealous of necros, lol)&nbsp; The junk mobs that CAN be AE kited don't drop any loot that bards are looking for... unless you are talking about TS items.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And you know what?&nbsp; If AE kiting is something that is a detriment to the performance of YOUR server, then you damn well better compensate me for taking away that ability.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This whole situation is ridiculous.&nbsp; But like I said earlier.. SOE has zero intention of listening to their customers and that is why SWG is failing, that is why EQ will fail, and that is why EQ2 will fail.&nbsp; What did Brenlo say a few months ago?&nbsp; No new nerfs... yeah sure thing Brenlo... at least we know what your word is worth now.</DIV>
